    "While this comparison focuses on only die cost which is the dominating cost in a system, a comprehensive end-to-end cost comparison between the 2D and 3D systems would include additional factors such as assembly costs, thermal cooling costs, off-chip HBM costs, testing costs, additional I/O costs, and packaging costs [50] [51].",
